Immediate next steps aligned with project priorities:
1. Start with Token/Context Optimization: add progressive tool disclosure, lazy schema loading, schema compression to Go core to cut tool context bloat by 90% as targeted.
2. Build Go core boilerplate first: LLMClient interface with automatic tier fallback for quota errors, SQLite with vector extension for L1/L2 dual memory, MCP router/client/server with deferred binary startup and small loaded tool caps (16 soft, 24 hard).
3. Port all functionality from upstream metamcp and jules-app (not deprecated robertpelloni forks) into Go core. Document parity progress in CHANGELOG.md, bump version to 0.2.0, commit and push.
4. Initialize dynamic tool discovery engine: scrape bookmark URLs, parse MCP/OpenAPI manifests, seed SQLite tool registry with initial entries from public MCP datasets.
5. Add auto model switching logic to Go core: catch 429 and 5xx errors, cascade to next configured model tier, update dashboard with active model, quota usage and fallback events.

Use Go goroutines for multi-model concurrency, isolate model threads to prevent crash propagation. Align with lightweight native UI plan (no Electron) for future frontends. Proceed autonomously, commit/push after each major step.
